{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Fret not thyself because of evildoers,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "neither be thou envious against the workers of iniquity."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For they shall soon be cut down like the grass,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and wither as the green herb."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Trust in the LORD, and do good;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "so shalt thou dwell in the land, and verily thou shalt be fed."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "37.3 verily: Heb. in truth, or, stableness"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Delight thyself also in the LORD;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and he shall give thee the desires of thine heart."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Commit thy way unto the LORD;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "trust also in him; and he shall bring it to pass."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "37.5 Commit…: Heb. Roll thy way upon"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he shall bring forth thy righteousness as the light,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and thy judgment as the noonday."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Rest in the LORD, and wait patiently for him:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "fret not thyself because of him who prospereth in his way,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "because of the man who bringeth wicked devices to pass."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "37.7 Rest in: Heb. Be silent to"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Cease from anger, and forsake wrath:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "fret not thyself in any wise to do evil."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For evildoers shall be cut off:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "but those that wait upon the LORD, they shall inherit the earth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For yet a little while, and the wicked shall not be:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "yea, thou shalt diligently consider his place, and it shall not be."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 11,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But the meek shall inherit the earth;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and shall delight themselves in the abundance of peace."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The wicked plotteth against the just,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and gnasheth upon him with his teeth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "37.12 plotteth: or, practiseth"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The Lord shall laugh at him:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "for he seeth that his day is coming."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The wicked have drawn out the sword,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and have bent their bow,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "to cast down the poor and needy,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and to slay such as be of upright conversation."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "37.14 such…: Heb. the upright of way"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Their sword shall enter into their own heart,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and their bows shall be broken."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A little that a righteous man hath is better than the riches of many wicked."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For the arms of the wicked shall be broken:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "but the LORD upholdeth the righteous."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The LORD knoweth the days of the upright:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and their inheritance shall be for ever."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They shall not be ashamed in the evil time:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and in the days of famine they shall be satisfied."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But the wicked shall perish,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and the enemies of the LORD shall be as the fat of lambs:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "they shall consume; into smoke shall they consume away."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "37.20 the fat: Heb. the preciousness"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The wicked borroweth, and payeth not again:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "but the righteous sheweth mercy, and giveth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For such as be blessed of him shall inherit the earth;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and they that be cursed of him shall be cut off."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The steps of a good man are ordered by the LORD:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and he delighteth in his way."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "37.23 ordered: or, established"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Though he fall, he shall not be utterly cast down:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "for the LORD upholdeth him with his hand."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I have been young, and now am old;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "yet have I not seen the righteous forsaken,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "nor his seed begging bread."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 26,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He is ever merciful, and lendeth;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and his seed is blessed."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "37.26 ever: Heb. all the day"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Depart from evil, and do good;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and dwell for evermore."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For the LORD loveth judgment,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and forsaketh not his saints; they are preserved for ever:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "but the seed of the wicked shall be cut off."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 29,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The righteous shall inherit the land,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and dwell therein for ever."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 30,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The mouth of the righteous speaketh wisdom,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and his tongue talketh of judgment."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 31,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The law of his God is in his heart;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "none of his steps shall slide."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "37.31 steps: or, goings"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 32,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The wicked watcheth the righteous,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and seeketh to slay him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 33,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The LORD will not leave him in his hand,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "nor condemn him when he is judged."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 34,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Wait on the LORD, and keep his way,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and he shall exalt thee to inherit the land:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "when the wicked are cut off, thou shalt see it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 35,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I have seen the wicked in great power,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and spreading himself like a green bay tree."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "37.35 a green…: or, a green tree that groweth in his own soil"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 36,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Yet he passed away, and, lo, he was not:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "yea, I sought him, but he could not be found."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 37,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Mark the perfect man, and behold the upright:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "for the end of that man is peace."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 38,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But the transgressors shall be destroyed together:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "the end of the wicked shall be cut off."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 39,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But the salvation of the righteous is of the LORD:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "he is their strength in the time of trouble."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 40,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the LORD shall help them, and deliver them:"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "he shall deliver them from the wicked, and save them,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "because they trust in him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}